HEADWORD: Shovelhead
<hw>Shov"el*head`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A shark (<spn>Sphryna tiburio</spn>) allied to the hammerhead, and
native of the warmer parts of the Atlantic and Pacific oceans; -- called
also <altname>bonnet shark</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shovelnose</ent>⟦br⟧
